issue.title: Fix CUDA 11.6 build error on Windows

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: 
A Windows SDK header #defines `small`, which clashes with a typedef in the CUDA 11.6 (and possibly other versions) headers.

Add an indirection for including cub.cuh that undefines `small`.

**Motivation and Context**
#11227

issue.title: Fix CUDA 11.6 build error on Windows

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: 
Avoid windows header that defines 'small' using suggestion from @cloudhan. 

We only apply the WIN32_LEAN_AND_MEAN flag to the CUDA provider to limit its effect.

**Motivation and Context**
Fix #11227 with cleaner approach than #11314
